com.conichi.sdk.key

Interface DoorOpeningCallback


  • public interface DoorOpeningCallback

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onOpeningFailed(DoorlockException exception)
      Called when an exception happened while try to locate, connect or interact with a door lock unit.
      void onOpeningFinished()
      Called when the door opening process has been finished.
      void onOpeningStarted()
      Called when the vendor SDK has found a doorlock unit and started opening it.

    • Method Detail

      • onOpeningStarted

        void onOpeningStarted()
        Called when the vendor SDK has found a doorlock unit and started opening it.

        NOTE: This method can be called multiple times since vendor's SDK might try to connect to different devices or perform many attempts to open a single door lock unit.

      • onOpeningFinished

        void onOpeningFinished()
        Called when the door opening process has been finished.

        NOTE: Not for every door provider receiving this callback means that the door has been successfully opened. This only means that the vendor's SDK has finished all the communications with a door lock.

      • onOpeningFailed

        void onOpeningFailed(DoorlockException exception)
        Called when an exception happened while try to locate, connect or interact with a door lock unit.
        Parameters:
        exception - an exception happend while trying to open a door.
